  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6981 sitting just below the massive 7000 gamma wall (14.6B), dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push above 7000 to hedge their long gamma exposure. The PIN regime confirms dealers will provide liquidity by selling rallies and buying dips, creating strong magnetic pull around current levels with the 6893 flip strike providing downside support. Watch for rejection at 7000 and potential mean reversion back toward 6950-6975 range, with the stacked positive gamma walls above 7000 creating significant resistance through 7100.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect the market to get capped near 7000 and chop sideways to lower.",
